data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Unlike other simulators out there, this simulator will regrade up to the target grade a number of times specified by the "Iterations" field and generate a report. This report will give average values per item successfully regraded to the target grade.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: Absolutely not, the more iterations you enter the more average the results will be. In the end, RNG is RNG, you can see how widely individual results will vary by using only one iteration. I suggest using the average values as a basis for determining if it is worth buying an item at grade, or regrading it yourself. Good luck!

data.name: label12.Text
data.value:
Some people claim that the RNG ArcheAge uses tends to result in more failures than it should. This option adds a bit higher failure rate to regrades, if you are one of those who believe this is the case, by increasing the odds of failure for every success, resetting when a failure occurs. It typically affects the results by a factor of 5-10% more failures.
I do NOT recommend using this feature when calculating for the Eternal grade. As Eternal already takes a bit of time without this feature enabled, you may be waiting a while for results.

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: May 2017 there was a regrade event in which all regrades up to and including unique got a 1.5x success rate added to them. Additionally, the chance for celestial grade gear to break was removed. This option mimics this event. If there is ever another event where the details regarding regrades change, I will update this program to reflect that change.
